About Creedence Clearwater Revival: 
Creedence Clearwater Revival’s 1968 self-titled debut album introduced the world to guitar-playing brothers John and Tom Fogerty, drummer Doug Clifford, and bassist Stu Cook, four young men out of El Cerrito in the San Francisco Bay Area. Though they emerged in a place and time where trippy psychedelic visions were the order of the day, CCR bucked the trends and instead tapped into a rich, traditional seam of American music that connected to blues, country, rockabilly, gospel, folk and R&B.    

During their short time together as a band (1968 – 1972), the band enjoyed an unparalleled period of creativity lead by singer, songwriter, arranger John Fogerty. They’ve sold close to 100 million records, releasing 14 Top 10 hits. They also managed to play over 150 tour dates around the world, including a headlining spot at Woodstock.

Creedence Clearwater Revival’s canon has become a part of the Great American Songbook. Fogerty penned songs like “Bad Moon Rising,” “Down on the Corner,” “Fortunate Son,” “Have You Ever Seen the Rain,” “Proud Mary,” “Born on the Bayou,” “Travelin’ Band” and “Up Around the Bend” have been ingrained into pop culture — not just as rock staples, but as classic standards.

With so many memorable songs that continue to grace our radio waves, television and movie screens, plus lyrics that still resonate today, Creedence Clearwater Revival is, truly, America’s greatest rock ’n’ roll band.

#ccr #creedenceclearwaterrevival #fortunateson

snippet.description:

Lyrics:
I could be the twist
The one to make you stop
The icing on your cake
The cherry on the top
It’s heaven in my heart
And we could find you some space
I could be the world to you
The missing piece
That extra sentimental kind of chemistry
Some people make it hard
With me that isn’t the case
Cos I make it so easy to fall in love
So come give me a call
and we’ll fall into us
I’m the perfect mix of Saturday night
And the rest of your life
Anyone with a heart would agree
It’s so easy
To fall in love with
The way I do my hair
The way you make me laugh
The way we love to share
A walk in Central Park
I could be fresh air
Might be the girl of your dreams
There’s no need to hide
If you’re into me cos I’m into you
Quite intimately
And maybe one night could turn into three
Well I’m down to see
Cos I make it so easy to fall in love
So come give me a call
And we’ll fall into us
I’m the perfect mix of Saturday night
And the rest of your life
Anyone with a heart would agree
It’s so easy to fall in love with me

 ---------------------------------

#OliviaDean #SoEasyToFallInLove #TheGrahamNortonShow

— This video is a fan-made concept trailer, created solely for artistic and entertainment purposes.The goal behind this trailer is to showcase my creativity and storytelling skills through a concept trailer based on a unique and original idea. By combining various effects, sound design, and AI technologies, I’ve crafted a cinematic experience that reimagines familiar worlds in bold and imaginative ways. This trailer is not official and is intended to entertain, inspire, and engage with the YouTube community. Thank you for your support — now let’s dive into a world shaped by creativity and craft. 🎬✨

— In this concept trailer for Spider-Man: Brand New Day, the story follows an older, emotionally scarred Peter Parker from Andrew Garfield’s universe, set after the events of No Way Home, as he struggles with a life defined by loss and unresolved guilt following Gwen Stacy’s death. Haunted by fractured memories that blur past failure with fleeting redemption, Peter is pulled back into the multiversal conflict when a desperate call for help emerges from another Spider-Man, signaling that the consequences of broken timelines are far from over. As echoes of sacrifice, second chances, and unfinished responsibility collide, the narrative positions Peter at a crossroads where personal grief and greater duty intersect, forcing him to confront whether redemption is still possible and whether one universe’s mistakes can threaten them all.

What is Roblox? ROBLOX is an online virtual playground and workshop, where kids of all ages can safely interact, create, have fun, and learn. It’s unique in that practically everything on ROBLOX is designed and constructed by members of the community. ROBLOX is designed for 13 to 18 year olds, but it is open to people of all ages. Each player starts by choosing an avatar and giving it an identity. They can then explore ROBLOX — interacting with others by chatting, playing games, or collaborating on creative projects. Each player is also given their own piece of undeveloped real estate along with a virtual toolbox with which to design and build anything — be it a navigable skyscraper, a working helicopter, a giant pinball machine, a multiplayer “Capture the Flag” game or some other, yet-to-be-dreamed-up creation. There is no cost for this first plot of virtual land. By participating and by building cool stuff, ROBLOX members can earn specialty badges as well as ROBLOX dollars (“Robux”). In turn, they can shop the online catalog to purchase avatar clothing and accessories as well as premium building materials, interactive components, and working mechanisms.

snippet.title: Life is Strange: Reunion Reveal Livestream
snippet.description:
Developed by Deck Nine Games, LIFE IS STRANGE: REUNION will launch on PlayStation 5®, Xbox Series X|S, and PC on March 26, 2026.

LIFE IS STRANGE: REUNION will be available in three editions: Standard, Deluxe, and Twin Pack.

Full details on each Edition can be found at http://lifeisstrange.com .

Chloe Price was Max Caulfield’s partner in time… Losing her is Max’s greatest regret.
 
Now Chloe has come to Caledon University. Haunted by nightmares and impossible memories, Chloe needs Max’s help. 

But Max is already in crisis: in three days, a deadly inferno will destroy the campus. 

Max’s Rewind power has bought her time – but she can’t prevent the blaze alone.

The fire will force Max and Chloe to make devastating decisions. Can they find a future together… Before everything burns?

snippet.title: MC 張天賦 - 無名氏 Perfect Strangers (Official Music Video)
snippet.description:
MC 張天賦 - 無名氏 Perfect Strangers (Official Music Video)

MC 張天賦 溫馨提示《無名氏》
不問回報的好人依然存在，請你繼續相信善良

請別忘記，
這座冰冷的小島上，
每天都有不同的溫暖故事正在發生。

例如，
黑雨之中，會有路人為你撐傘擋雨；
當你沒帶零錢坐巴士時，會有陌生人替你付費；
走在街上，會有無名氏拍拍你的肩膀，
提醒你背包的拉鏈沒拉好。

如果某天，
你發現你對這種不問回報的善意有所疑惑，
突然變得不太理解，
請容許我再次溫馨提示：
請你，繼續相信善良。

#MC張天賦 #無名氏 #PerfectStrangers 

——————

曲：陳可為 / 齊樂平
詞：黃偉文
編：Dick Wong / 周錫漢
監：周錫漢

誰於街角提醒我 扒手想過來開鎖
誰撐起傘來遮我 如果黑雨淋濕我
去坐巴士錢不夠 你來付費請我坐
跟你是好友麽 為何熱心幫我

明明不需要 待我好
為何竟普照 我路途 
其實你 不過路人
回頭就 再找不到
小恩賜 大美好
給悲劇都市 還原 樂觀指數
讓人間 接近消失的光 再望到 

掛念簡單的相處 各懷善意的偶遇
自何日失信心 懷疑另有意思

明明不需要 待我好
為何竟普照 我路途  
其實你 不過路人 
回頭就 再找不到
小恩賜 大美好
給悲劇都市 還原 樂觀指數
讓人間 接近消失的光 再望到 

願傳頌 你的好
好比旱地種 薰衣草 
無名氏 毋問回報                  
留芳於瘠土                     

明明心灰了 又碰到
如羣星普照 我路途  
無限個 親切路人 潛藏在 冷冰冰小島
心穿了 為我補
感激遇到你 證實仁慈並非 是少數
近乎哭 你就伸出雙手 抱抱 

羣星隱進人海裏
從不需要誰嘉許
如這恩我還不了
餘溫等我傳開去

snippet.title: "Piece of Denmark" - Marsh Family parody of "Piece of My Heart" by Erma Franklin on Greenland/Trump
snippet.description:
This is a hasty cover of Erma Franklin's 1967 belter, written by Jerry Ragovoy and Bert Berns, that is one of our favourite soul tracks, and only lost out to a Grammy to her younger sister Aretha in 1969 ("Chain of Fools"). It had a resurgence in Europe in the early 90s after the end of the Cold War thanks to a Levi jeans advert, and its highest chart position for the re-release was number 5 ... in Denmark.

Our treatment pays tribute to the Danes (who suffered proportionally among the highest casualties in wars supporting the USA after its triggering the collective security clauses of NATO in places like Iraq and Afghanistan), and who are being shaken down at the moment by the likes of Trump, Vance, and Miller in their bid to bully Europe to agree to the annexation of autonomous Greenlanders. You probably don't need a link to make sense of this, as it's all over the news, but in case: https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/articles/c4g5345ylk0o. 

There are (again) some rude words in our parody lyrics, for which apologies, as we continue to respond to stress by swearing, which can actually be very cathartic and good for you, as long as you can stop it spreading to your kids: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hypoalgesic_effect_of_swearing. 

___________________________ 

Support us here: 
- PayPal to leave us a tip jar: https://paypal.me/marshfamilysongs 
- Patreon for ongoing support & bonuses: https://www.patreon.com/marshfamilysongs 
- Crowdfunder for debut album out in 2026: https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/marshfamily/the-marsh-family-debut-album-campaign 

Find our other channels here: https://linktr.ee/marshfamilysongs 

Follow us here: 
- https://www.marshfamilysongs.com 
- https://www.facebook.com/MarshFamilySongs/ 
- https://www.instagram.com/marshfamilysongs/ 
- https://twitter.com/MarshSongs 
- https://www.threads.net/@marshfamilysongs 
- https://www.tiktok.com/@marshfamilysongs 
- https://bsky.app/profile/marshfamilysongs.bsky.social 
- https://open.spotify.com/artist/6AYmbCwi92V29y69lkRkRa 

___________________________

LYRICS

Didn’t Danes show their steel when you fought the Taliban?
Didn’t they give you everything – when you reckon per capita?
But, with all the stuff they gave ya, it’s never enough …
The guy-toddler bone-spur baby’s grabbing Greenland in a huff!

So, come on … come on … come on … come on …
It’s a mother-f&*king piece of Denmark, he’s crazy! (BREAK IT!)
Break another old alliance apart, for money?! (HAVE A…)
Have another little change of the heart, now, maybe?!
You know he’s lost it if he’s threatening Nuuk!

He’s flouting the peace (DOIN’ NO GOOD)
Congress knows deep down in their heart, that it ain’t right
But oh, they’ll never, never stop him till defeat’s in sight, oh …
He tells us all, there’ll be tariffs and pain
But when it’s NATO up in arms, he’s selling out friends:

So Donald … Donald … Donald … Donald: quit it

You know it’s rotten but it makes him feel good

It’s a mother-f&*king piece of Denmark, he’s crazy!

Have the 25th Amendment kickstart, now maybe?!

localized.title: "Piece of Denmark" - Marsh Family parody of "Piece of My Heart" by Erma Franklin on Greenland/Trump
localized.description:
This is a hasty cover of Erma Franklin's 1967 belter, written by Jerry Ragovoy and Bert Berns, that is one of our favourite soul tracks, and only lost out to a Grammy to her younger sister Aretha in 1969 ("Chain of Fools"). It had a resurgence in Europe in the early 90s after the end of the Cold War thanks to a Levi jeans advert, and its highest chart position for the re-release was number 5 ... in Denmark.

Our treatment pays tribute to the Danes (who suffered proportionally among the highest casualties in wars supporting the USA after its triggering the collective security clauses of NATO in places like Iraq and Afghanistan), and who are being shaken down at the moment by the likes of Trump, Vance, and Miller in their bid to bully Europe to agree to the annexation of autonomous Greenlanders. You probably don't need a link to make sense of this, as it's all over the news, but in case: https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/articles/c4g5345ylk0o. 

There are (again) some rude words in our parody lyrics, for which apologies, as we continue to respond to stress by swearing, which can actually be very cathartic and good for you, as long as you can stop it spreading to your kids: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hypoalgesic_effect_of_swearing.

snippet.title: Pre-Order Trailer | Marathon
snippet.description:
Marathon releases March 5, 2026. 

Secrets. Buried and rotting. With the UESC holding the shovel.  
That's where you come in, Runner.

Scavenge the lost colony of Tau Ceti IV in the survival extraction FPS from the creators of Halo and Destiny.

Pre-order Marathon now: 
Steam: https://store.steampowered.com/app/3065800/Marathon/
PlayStation 5: https://www.playstation.com/en-us/games/marathon/
Xbox Series X|S: https://www.microsoft.com/store/productid/9p8mgmxndv9b

Learn more: https://bung.ie/4rl5QfF

TikTok: https://tiktok.com/@marathonthegame

Twitter: https://x.com/marathonthegame
Bluesky: https://bsky.app/profile/marathonthegame.bungie.net
Discord: https://discord.gg/marathonthegame
